# Depth Analyse

**Raspberry Pi 5 based 360° Groove Detection System** using a continuous rotation servo and ToF sensor.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

**Depth Analyse** is a non-contact groove/depth measurement system built on the Raspberry Pi 5. It rotates a specimen (or the sensor) using a **MG996R 360° continuous rotation servo** while measuring distance with a **VL53L0X Time-of-Flight sensor** at regular angular intervals.

The system detects grooves by comparing measured distance against a calculated surface baseline and generates both CSV data and a visual graph.

---

## 🎯 What We Tried to Build

We wanted to create an **automated angular depth scanner** that can:

- Rotate 360° continuously using a hobby servo
- Take distance readings at every 2° interval
- Identify grooves/depressions on a surface
- Report groove depth, angular position, and width
- Work reliably on Raspberry Pi 5 (which has stricter GPIO requirements)

